The paper focuses on analyzing the coverage and spectral efficiency of a downlink cellular network, which involves the use of information theory, networking, and optimization techniques. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also uses the alpha-beta-gamma (ABG) path-loss model to analyze urban macro (UMa) and urban micro (UMi) deployments, which falls under the category of cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The paper also discusses the optimization of available spectral resources, which can be categorized under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
